Sure, here are some example sentences using the Serbian word "piće" (пиће) in different forms and positions:

1. *Piće* je hladno. (The *drink* is cold.)
2. Nisam siguran koje *piće* da naručim. (I'm not sure which *drink* to order.)
3. Dali su mi besplatno *piće* u baru. (They gave me a free *drink* at the bar.)
4. Sutra idemo u kupovinu *pića*. (Tomorrow we're going shopping for *drinks*.)
5. Oni vole da piju bezalkoholna *pića*. (They like to drink non-alcoholic *beverages*.)
6. *Piće* koje sam naručio je jako slatko. (The *drink* I ordered is very sweet.)
7. Konobar je došao da mi donese *piće*. (The waiter came to bring me a *drink*.)
8. Želela bih da naručim isto *piće* kao moj prijatelj. (I would like to order the same *drink* as my friend.)
9. Da li imate nešto osvežavajuće za *piće*? (Do you have something refreshing to *drink*?)
10. *Piće* koje sam probao juče nije mi se svidelo. (The *drink* I tried yesterday didn't taste good to me.)

I hope these sentences help you understand how the word "piće" can be used in Serbian.